void eol_loader_read_string_from_file ( char **  data,
eolFile *  file 
)

read string data from an open eolFile buffer. does nothing if the file handle is NULL or opened for writing.

Parameters:
data a pointer to a char pointer. If the char pointer is not null, it will be used otherwise a buffer will be allocated for the string in question and must be freed separately.
file the file handle to read from
